LongDescription: A smaller off-shoot of the intelligence center which assists in speeding up their work.
FlavorText:
In short, it's a compartment hooked up to an AN-2500 Superbrain. You won't find a more robust computer system in the Alliance, hands down. Outdated control interface (an Alliance specialty) but tough, reliable, and easy to maintain. MazTronics is pretty proud of this one and while that would normally be a cause for concern, it's actually an effective piece of hardware that services every planet in Alliance territory, even the Separatists.

Most of the time, Superbrains are used for communications, especially since we switched over from satellite beams to pulse waveforms, and as an added bonus you can access the ANET to stay up-to-date on the latest Slam Kings game. On the export market, fellas close to the Alliance are always thirsty to get their hands on a Superbrain.

- S. Ace, CWO
